      "text": {
        "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Problem\">Problem</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2016_APMO_Problems/Problem_1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Problem\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>We say that a triangle <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/2/a/e2a559986ed5a0ffc5654bd367c29dfc92913c36.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$ABC$\" width=\"42\" height=\"13\" /> is great if <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/The\" title=\"The\">the</a> following holds: for any point <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/f/f/9ffb448918db29f2a72f8f87f421b3b3cad18f95.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$D$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"17\" height=\"14\" /> on the side <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/c/5/6c52a41dcbd739f1d026c5d4f181438b75b76976.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$BC$\" width=\"28\" height=\"12\" />, if <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/b/4/4b4cade9ca8a2c8311fafcf040bc5b15ca507f52.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$P$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/8/6/9866e3a998d628ba0941eb4fea0666ac391d149a.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$Q$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"13\" height=\"16\" /> are the feet of the perpendiculars from <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/f/f/9ffb448918db29f2a72f8f87f421b3b3cad18f95.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$D$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"17\" height=\"14\" /> to the lines <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/5/7/e/57ee5125358c0606c9b588580ddfa66f83e607b7.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$AB$\" width=\"27\" height=\"13\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/1/7/a179ff2638e4799cadd820db205c2beff6299ce9.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$AC$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"30\" height=\"14\" />, respectively, then the reflection of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/f/f/9ffb448918db29f2a72f8f87f421b3b3cad18f95.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$D$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"17\" height=\"14\" /> in the line <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/7/a/b/7ab17967324fc2b12349c0610c6c256f4c829162.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$PQ$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"27\" height=\"16\" /> lies on the circumcircle of the triangle <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/2/a/e2a559986ed5a0ffc5654bd367c29dfc92913c36.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$ABC$\" width=\"42\" height=\"13\" />. Prove that triangle <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/2/a/e2a559986ed5a0ffc5654bd367c29dfc92913c36.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$ABC$\" width=\"42\" height=\"13\" /> is great if and only if <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/a/4/ea494684dc60997279257d5a54e877a1fb28ca60.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\angle A = 90^{\\circ}$\" width=\"74\" height=\"13\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/3/a/f3ac37c9fa391eebb9601bfaca8bfbfaabdf5ca1.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$AB = AC$\" width=\"80\" height=\"13\" />.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution\">Solution</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2016_APMO_Problems/Problem_1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Solution\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240908051128\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.020 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.021 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 132/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 292/1000000\nPost窶親xpand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post窶親xpand size: 2206/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,templat